March 5th, 2023 marked 2 years since my knee injury! I had partially torn my ACL, my meniscus was hanging on by a thread, I had contusions on my femur and tibia and a fracture on my medial tibial plateau. It was by far the worst injury I've ever had (and this is coming from someone who broke BOTH hands at the same time!)

In total, it took 14 months for me to fully recover 100%. My goal was to get back to doing everything I was able to do on March 4th, 2021. I had to work harder than ever before in order to do what I love most. I'm forever grateful for the friends and family that supported me during that sad time. In this video I share my progression of not being able to walk properly to eventually doing flips again! 

Handstands and rope manipulation kept me sane and made me stronger. As my flexibility in my knee became better, so did my ability to apply weight on my leg. 

Sometimes these setbacks are a reminder of what really matters to you. For me, nothing felt more important than getting back into performing and being creative. If you're currently dealing with a setback, I'm here to tell you to keep pushing yourself because in the end, it's worth it 😎
